line_1: And Earth the humble Object scorn'd.
Than flattery the world has scorn'd,
line_2: NO theme the poet more has mourn'd,

line_1: Nay even the lesser Genius was not scorn'd,
line_2: But each to his desert with praise adorn'd;

line_1: Ere noblest Dames the artful Shuttle scorn'd:
line_2: THUS Tapistry of old, the Walls adorn'd,

line_1: Courted by flattery, but by merit scorn'd,
line_2: By titles stain'd, with beauty unadorn'd,

line_1: My Grave is fill'd, and grac'd with what he scorn'd:
line_2: Let not the Nymph upbraid, when shes return'd,

line_1: The mighty myriads, now securely scorn'd,
line_2: With helmed heads and dragon scales adorn'd,

line_1: All witnesses of blessings foully scorn'd,
line_2: And life abus'd — and not to be suborn'd.
